values: Hi everyone! Sorry I have rather disappeared from here lately! I've had some real life stuff come up along the same time as my computer problems and I just kind of found myself moving offline for a bit. But I do hope to come back on here...right now I'm working on getting Photoshop back onto my computer again so I can start creating icons and having more fun! But that may be a little ways a way. But in case you were curious about what was taking over my life...I have to introduce my two new house mates...Buddy and Dia! Those two are Formosan Mountain Dogs that were rescued from Taiwan and flown over here for adoption! We've had Buddy, the black and white one, for about three months now and Dia has been with us for just under 2 weeks. They've both about 6-7 months old and completely taking over my life! LoL In a good way! So here's hoping that everyone is doing great and I look forward to getting caught up with you all!

It occurred to me that I just kind of disappeared from here without warning and that I'm sure a few of you were wondering what was going on. Since I hadn't after all finished posting a few episodes worth of screen captures. 

Well what sadly happened was failure of my external hard drive, which was where I was storing all my anime and all my lovely raws. So I'm still hopeful that I can recover the data and pick up where I left off, but its proven to be a real difficult case in attempting to get copies of some of those older raws I had as well. So hence I haven't been capturing like I use to. With lots of luck though you'll see me back in the upcoming weeks posting new goodies! And finishing up some of the series that remain undone at this point!

Sorry for those of you who followed me devotedly with a particular series, I only hope you can find some goodies to tide you over while I attempt to recover!

Oh for the first time in a long time I felt the urge to go ahead and post a batch of icons. Mostly because all this snow falling on my house is making me crave snowy icons! LoL So you'll have to put up with a bunch of them this round. And well if this snow keeps falling probably even more later on! ^^ Kuroshitsuji x14 Vampire Knight x12 Berserk x12 Capeta x5 Claymore x6 Devil May Cry x1 D. Gray-man x2 Jigoku Shoujo x1 Samurai Deeper Kyo x1 Yami no Matsuei x1 Full Metal Panic x3

This is a REDO of a series that I did several months ago; at the time I only did a quick grouping of captures for my own screen capturing purposes from some RAWs. Now I have the DVDs so I went ahead and did a more thorough capturing the series. To give you an example on the original set I did I averaged between 300-400 captures an episode. On this run I don't think I did one episode with less than 800 captures to its name. ^^ And since some fellow SPR fans expressed and interested I'm going to go ahead and share this group as well. Who knows maybe I can get even more lovely GH icons out of you guys! LoL I have to admit redoing the series really has inspired me to make some more Naru icons. Heheh

Same rules are usual, if you're new here you can find my screen capture rules under my User Profile. And of course comments are luv and keep me sharing my screen captures. LoL

Ok so I'm sitting here being a good girl and vegging out by watching some of my fave scenes from Ghost Hunt episode 25 when my brain clicks...wait...this scene doesn't look familiar...eeeps missing scenes!! Now I have to go through every single one of the DVD and check for scenes that I don't recognize. LoL Darn you for showing cut versions on TV!!

LoL And well now that I have the DVD's I'll also be redoing my screen captures for the series...if anyone is interested in having me post them again let me know. Might get me motivated to make new icons. Hehehe

So I'm abit bored today and I figured I might as well have some fun and post some randomness for you guys to look at! LoL So tonights post while I fight to make Kuroshitsuji icons is my baby dragons! ^^ If you click on them you help them grow up to be nice adult dragons and not die a horrible abandoned death. LoL

By Request! I'm a bit of a fan of Naruto, but I have to admit this is probably my least favorite of the OVA's or Specials. But hey if its requested and I have it I'll post it. ^^ So enjoy.

By Request! Well those of you who know me know I try to include some scenery shots in amid the character shots I take for screen captures. But I still want to give a word of warning, there are tons of scenery shots in this collection. I can't help but think as much attention to detail that is given to the backgrounds that I had to screen capture them with the same care as I did the characters. For those who don't know 5 centimers per second is a movie that tells three short stories dealing with love. Its very sweet and quite sad to watch but one of those I recommend wholeheartedly. ^^ For one thing is very very pretty.

Not that this series needs much help to be a joy. LoL Beautiful characters, lovely plots, and a stunning backdrop make this one of my fave series of the new season. So if you like a bit of mystery with your bishies check this series out!

Such an incredibly moving movie, so sweet, sad, funny and just an emotional roller coaster all around. I've seen the animes series and I was a bit annoyed at all the unanswered questions. The series is great don't get me wrong, but I hate not understanding a plot point. LoL And well the movie differs just enough from the anime to explain all those points yet not lose your attention by thinking this is a completely different show. ^^ So I highly recommend checking it out, even with the different anime style and voice actors than from the TV series.

While I am a huge fan of this manga I'm actually not that big of a fan of the anime series. Partially because of small changes to the storyline but probably most because theres no really good groups doing the subbing so I spend half the time annoyed with translations. Yes I am really picky but darn it I am completely in love with the art style that is shown here. Even the most violent scene is done with such style and beauty. It makes it completely impossible for me not to do screen captures for this series.

Oh side note: I wasn't able to get a very good copy of episode #4, most of the show was fine but there were points in the action scenes where the video would glitch andI wasn't able to capture, so if I can find a better version I'll do another set of those at a later time.

Hello all! Ok this is more for my own strange mindset than anything else but since I put it all together I figured I might as well tell you guys about it! LoL I went ahead and created two communities, not really for community sake though. What they are essentially are my screen capture and icon archives. A way to find everything I've uploaded without having to dig through my strange ramblings to locate them! Whoohoo! LoL So you can find the links over to the right there and I'll also list them in this post just for your own references. ^^

You can join them if you want but I'll also be updating this site with my newest things as well so don't worry about missing anything if you don't join. ^^

Aww new computers are such wonderful things. Especially when they're faster, stronger and even prettier than the one you had before. But even more so when the little alien on the front of it causes gamers everywhere to go "Ooooooooh!" in wonder at the site of its flashy lights...


At least until you realize as you finish wiping clean the hard drive of your old computer that you completely forgot to move Photoshop and all of the brushes, textures, and gradients you spent years collecting from the old computer to the new one...

Somehow...I feel like crying...

Hello all! Man sorry I've been so absent lately from all your convo's and postings! I'm afraid life interfered with my fun quite a bit and I haven't had time to play on the internet nearly as much as I'd like too!

But I'm working on my schedule so I can have time to play every day as well as get my work done! LoL

Oh but the real reason I'm posting is I'm starting up a new community here on LJ and I wanted to invite you guys and pretty much just let you check it out and see what you think of the concept. It's one of I've been considering for a while. And honestly I haven't managed to find any like it on here so I figured I might as well. So if you're interested please check out my new little site. ^^

http://community.livejournal.com/animecaps/

Hope everyone's doing great! And I hope to post some more icons this week as well so keep and eye out for those! Enjoy!

Wow I think this is the first time I've ever posted here without having screen captures or icons to dump! LoL But I was sitting around being depressed over the fact that almost all the animes I watch end their run this week or have already ended and all I could think is...crap!

What's really sad is looking at a list of upcoming animes I can't see anything that is really set to drag me in like this summer did. No more Claymore, DeathNote, Zombie Loan, Kaze no Stigma, Ghost Hunt, or Darker than Black. I need new animes so here's the real reason for this post...anyone have anything up coming that they can't wait to watch? ^^ Or something they're going to miss so much they're begging for a second season!

Man I can't believe that episode 11 is the end of this series, man I really hope the DVD's come out with extra episodes cause I'm not ready to give up on these characters yet darn it! LoL Thank god for the manga! Anyway so I was in a mood, which of course means I make icons and this time I felt rather animated. So a rather small batch of animated ZL icons. ^^ Enjoy!
